# AI Subject Guide & Question Bank — Walkthrough

## Project Structure

```
V2/
├── .env                  ← Your Groq API key (edit this!)
├── .env.example          ← Template
├── .gitignore
├── requirements.txt      ← All dependencies
├── config.py             ← Centralized settings
├── document_loader.py    ← PDF/DOCX → chunked Documents
├── vector_store.py       ← FAISS embedding + persistence
├── rag_chain.py          ← LangChain QA with structured output
└── app.py                ← Streamlit frontend
```

---

## Architecture & Data Flow

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["📄 Upload PDF/DOCX"] --> B["document_loader.py"]
    B -->|Extract Text| C["Detect Doc Type"]
    C -->|Add Metadata| D["Chunk with RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter"]
    D --> E["vector_store.py"]
    E -->|Embed with all-MiniLM-L6-v2| F["FAISS Index"]
    F -->|Persist to disk| G["faiss_index/"]

    H["❓ User Question"] --> I["rag_chain.py"]
    F -->|Top-K retrieval| I
    I -->|Structured prompt| J["Groq LLM · llama-3.3-70b"]
    J --> K["📝 Structured Answer + Sources"]
```

---

## Module Breakdown

### [config.py](file:///f:/Education/Agentic_AI_Sesstion/Project/V2/config.py)
Single source of truth for all settings. Change model, chunk size, or top-k here — no other files touched.

### [document_loader.py](file:///f:/Education/Agentic_AI_Sesstion/Project/V2/document_loader.py)
- **PDF**: `PyPDF2` reads page-by-page, preserving page numbers for attribution
- **DOCX**: `python-docx` reads paragraphs
- **Type Detection**: Keyword patterns classify as `question_paper`, `lab_manual`, `notes`, or `general`
- **Chunking**: `RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter` (1000 chars, 200 overlap) splits on natural boundaries

### [vector_store.py](file:///f:/Education/Agentic_AI_Sesstion/Project/V2/vector_store.py)
- **Embeddings**: `all-MiniLM-L6-v2` runs locally (no API key needed)
- **FAISS**: In-memory similarity search, persisted to `faiss_index/`
- **Incremental merge**: New docs merge into existing index without rebuild

### [rag_chain.py](file:///f:/Education/Agentic_AI_Sesstion/Project/V2/rag_chain.py)
- **Prompt**: Enforces structured output (Definition → Key Concepts → Example → Steps → Practice Question)
- **Chain**: `RetrievalQA` with `stuff` strategy + source document tracking
- **Source attribution**: Deduped display of file name, doc type, page, chunk index

### [app.py](file:///f:/Education/Agentic_AI_Sesstion/Project/V2/app.py)
- **Sidebar**: File upload + process button + knowledge base info + reset
- **Main**: Chat-style Q&A with expandable source sections
- **Session state**: Persists vector store and chain across Streamlit reruns

---

## How to Run

### 1. Add your Groq API key
Edit [.env](file:///f:/Education/Agentic_AI_Sesstion/Project/V2/.env) — replace `gsk_your_api_key_here` with your key from [console.groq.com](https://console.groq.com)

### 2. Launch the app
```bash
cd f:\Education\Agentic_AI_Sesstion\Project\V2
streamlit run app.py
```

### 3. First run
The first launch downloads the embedding model (~80MB) — takes 1-2 minutes. Subsequent runs are instant.

### 4. Usage
1. Upload PDF/DOCX files in the sidebar
2. Click **Process Documents**
3. Ask questions in the chat input
4. View structured answers with source attribution

